nntpspider (0.1.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * reorganized verbosity levels. Normal mode is useful, verbose mode is
    still usable und debug mode now includes the server communication
  * added progress indicator when fetching the article headers
  * added progress indicator when fetching the grouplist
  * in debug mode even the nntp communication is monitored
  * some debug messages are printed to stderr

 -- Michael Mayer <mmayer@users.berlios.de>  Thu, 18 Mar 2004 11:02:30 +0100


nntpspider (0.1) unstable; urgency=high

  * a very big step forward. Now it's in real alpha state.
  * using commandline switches
  * configurable filenames for serverlist, resultlist and grouplist
  * differentiate three levels of verbosity: normal/verbose/debug mode
  * improved readability of the debug output
  * fixed many bugs in the connection error handling
  * Added a simple Makefile
  * using correct mail adress

 -- Michael Mayer <mmayer@users.berlios.de>  Wed, 10 Mar 2004 15:10:53 +0100


nntpspider (0.0.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial release

